          "distinct": true,
          "id": "4760f46ba46177af8c640d8a0ace87b9c87a09a0",
          "message": "fix(release): track canonical version in workspace root package.json\n\nPreviously workspace root stayed at 0.0.0 (a marker version) while\npublishable packages tracked the shipped version. That made the\nrelease PR body read \"previous: v0.0.0\" because create-release-pr.yml\nread base from root via jq, and forced readCanonicalVersion() into a\n\"pick first publishable, assert lockstep\" pattern that was harder to\nreason about.\n\nNow bump writes root + publishable packages together, and\nreadCanonicalVersion reads root and asserts publishable packages\nmatch. Anyone inspecting the repo's root package.json sees the\ncurrent shipped version. The lockstep error message also gets\nclearer (lists `<root>` alongside named packages).\n\nBumps root to 0.2.0 to align with the current shipped state.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
          "timestamp": "2026-04-27T20:12:35.296Z",
          "tree_id": "",
