          "distinct": true,
          "id": "1fc499ad2bb5f973db69bdfecb765cf1c0717abd",
          "message": "fix(release): attribute release-side effects to mikrodroid[bot]\n\nPreviously the publish job's tag push, GitHub Release author, and\nPR-preview comments showed up as github-actions[bot] because we used\nsecrets.GITHUB_TOKEN. The rolling release PR was already authored by\nmikrodroid[bot] (via the App token), so the release outputs looked\ninconsistent — same effort, two identities.\n\nMints the mikrodroid App token at the top of both the plan and\npublish jobs, then routes:\n\n  - plan: unlabel-preview → App token (the only side effect)\n  - publish: checkout (for git push auth), tag, github-release,\n    comment-pr → App token\n\nThe plan command's read-only PR/commit lookup stays on GITHUB_TOKEN\n(no attribution issue, doesn't need the App round-trip). npm publish\nunchanged — still uses NODE_AUTH_TOKEN.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
          "timestamp": "2026-04-27T21:05:22.465Z",
