          "distinct": true,
          "id": "9b7bf7c50b612d1336446d75c5e2eb4406a48169",
          "message": "feat(cli)!: make env vars secret by default\n\nRemoves the always-on/always-off split (`--secret`, `--secrets FILE`) in\nfavour of a single rule: every value is secret unless explicitly marked\notherwise. Closes the \"I forgot --secret\" foot-gun and keeps secret\nvalues out of shell history and `ps` output.\n\nBREAKING CHANGE:\n- `--secrets FILE` removed from `deploy`, `dev`, `test`, `sim/*`. Move\n  those entries into `.env` / `.env.<mode>` / `--env FILE`.\n- `--secret` removed from `mikro env set` and `mikro sim env set`.\n  `mikro env set KEY` (no VALUE) prompts for a hidden value and stores\n  it as a secret. To set a non-secret value, pass `VALUE` together with\n  `--no-secret`. Passing `VALUE` without `--no-secret` errors.\n- `.env` entries are now secret by default. Add a `# @no-secret`\n  comment line directly above an entry to mark just that one var as\n  visible in `mikro env list`.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
          "timestamp": "2026-05-02T14:21:36.769Z",
