          "distinct": true,
          "id": "6e63e295eb76e7c7fcf277f9a1e7436a4566982b",
          "message": "ci(release): cap pre-major bumps in mikrojs's own release flow\n\nAdopts the 0.x safety net for this project: every push-driven release\nPR runs `releaser bump` with `--breaking-is-minor-on-0x`, so a stray\n`feat!:` won't surprise-cut 1.0.0. The new workflow_dispatch `cut_major`\ninput is the explicit override for when we actually want the major.\n\nAlso drops the unused `--breaking-is-minor-on-0x` plumbing through\n`releaser plan` and `release.yml` — that path was scope creep; only\ncreate-release-pr.yml computes the bump that lands in package.json.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
