          "distinct": true,
          "id": "12c8f452cacd40c64d5a051012d8af2383f378ad",
          "message": "refactor(releaser): shorten pr-preview version to bare g<sha>\n\nThe timestamp was redundant with the SHA — both encode \"which build\" and\nthe SHA alone is enough to identify the commit being previewed. The\nPR-preview flow is one-shot per `labeled` event (label is removed after\npublish) so re-runs of the same SHA aren't expected.\n\nDrops the now-unused formatTimestamp/zeroPad helpers and the `now: Date`\nfield from BumpInputs.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
          "timestamp": "2026-05-02T21:17:00.799Z",
