          "distinct": true,
          "id": "8269c3f61a48999a3948c8e05d6e6e3d82b69558",
          "message": "feat(runtime): allocate QuickJS heap from PSRAM by default\n\nMitigates HTTPS handshake failures structurally on PSRAM-equipped\nchips: with the JS heap in external RAM, retained JS state no longer\nchips away at the contiguous internal SRAM that mbedTLS, WiFi/BLE,\nand DMA buffers depend on. Measured on esp32s3: internalLargestFree\nstays around 120 KB across 160 KB of retained ballast, vs collapsing\nto 12 KB and breaking handshake without this. Slower JS execution\n(higher PSRAM access latency) is invisible against typical IO-bound\nembedded workloads. No effect on hosts and chips without PSRAM.\n\nPlumbed via three platform hooks (malloc_psram / calloc_psram /\nrealloc_psram), a parallel mik__js_* allocator family that the\nQuickJS JSMallocFunctions route to, and a Kconfig option that\ndefaults on when CONFIG_SPIRAM=y.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
          "timestamp": "2026-05-10T14:18:29.989Z",
          "tree_id": "",
          "url": "https://github.com/mikrojs/mikrojs/commit/8269c3f61a48999a3948c8e05d6e6e3d82b69558"
