          "distinct": true,
          "id": "2f30f42f990cbe941d5f7092147526bff0c1ab61",
          "message": "feat!: replace .on/.off with Observable streams (#70)\n\n- Adds `mikrojs/observable`: a push-based, composable event stream primitive with a native C++ implementation and a JS operator package (`map`, `filter`, `take`, `takeUntil`, `finalize`). Composition via a single `pipe()` method; user-defined operators are first-class (`(source) => Observable`). Multicast factory: `Observable.withEmitters()` returns `{observable, next, complete}`.\n- Migrates the `.on/.off` event surface across `wifi`, `wifi.ap`, `ble.peripheral`, and the `udp.UdpSocket.onMessage` single-handler setter to `Observable<T>` properties. One native registration per event type fans out to all JS subscribers; UDP attaches lazily so the `dropped` counter semantics are preserved.\n- Errors are isolated to the offending subscriber: throws inside observer or operator callbacks are caught at the dispatch boundary and logged via `console.error` (matching the existing `mik_call_handler` precedent in the C runtime). Recoverable failures flow as `Result<Ok, Err>` values via `next` — typed via the second `Err` parameter.",
          "timestamp": "2026-05-10T20:50:07.350Z",
          "tree_id": "",
          "url": "https://github.com/mikrojs/mikrojs/commit/2f30f42f990cbe941d5f7092147526bff0c1ab61"
