          "distinct": true,
          "id": "616a2944ace3d160f76c5f243227b78c660e8f76",
          "message": "feat(runtime): add on-device file logging via `mikro logs pull` (#92)\n\nOpt-in via `logFile: true` in `mikro.config.ts`. Tees console + ESP_LOG output through a rotated file under `/logs`, with timestamps and a configurable flush policy.\n\n- New `mikro logs pull` command streams or archives the captured log via a CMD_FS_GET protocol op.\n- Consolidates log-related commands under one verb so wire-streaming (`tail`) lives alongside the file-pulling (`pull`)\n\nBREAKING CHANGE: `mikro tail` is removed. Use `mikro logs tail`.",
          "timestamp": "2026-05-13T21:17:26.078Z",
